If you want the moss to take on a greater amount of color, you can allow it to sit in the glycerin, water and dye solution for a greater amount of time. Remove the now-dyed and preserved moss. Squeeze out excess moisture. Dry as you would for other, non-dyed moss. Store in plastic bags until used in craft projects or other home projects.  You have successfully dried moss.
